The Maharashtra Regulation of Transfer of Government Employees and Prevention of Delays in the discharge of Government Duties Act, 2005.
The Government Court:

In accordance with the provisions of the Maharashtra Regulation of Transfer of Government Employees for the Purpose of Public Service and Prevention of Delay in the Performance of Government Duties Act, 2005, as recommended by the Civil Service Board and with the approval of the authorities competent to make the transfer, and in accordance with the provisions of sections 4 (4) (2) and 4 (5) of the said Act and the General Election to the Legislative Assembly 2024, the Government of Maharashtra has issued a notification to this effect. Election Commission of India Reference No. 1 here. As per the directions given in the letter dated 31.07.2024, the Government is ordering the replacement of Shri Kiran Kolpe, Group-A Cadre, Maharashtra Development Service, Group Development Officer, Panchayat Samiti, Deoni, G. Latur. The officer concerned is being posted in the position indicated in column no. 3 in front of his name.

02. The said order comes into immediate effect and the officer concerned shall join the post indicated in the order of posting forthwith. Also, the officers concerned should not go on unauthorised leave. Related to

para_trans: Government Adalat No: MAVISE-1024 / Q. No. 316/2024 Aastha-3 / AADEDSA No. 2

The attention of the officers is being drawn to the Government Circular No: CDR 1082/2567/28 XI, dated 30.08.1982 of the General Administration Department. They should note that if the officers concerned submit any form of application for change of posting / cancellation of appointment, they will be liable for disciplinary action as per the instructions in the said Government Circular.

03. In line with the General Assembly Elections-2024, Shri. The officers concerned are being transferred as per the aforesaid orders in accordance with the directions issued by the Election Commission of India and with the approval of the competent authority. Also, since the post of transfer / posting is related to election work, the concerned Divisional Commissioner / CEO, Zila Parishad should relieve the above officers from their present post with immediate effect and ask them to join their place of appointment immediately. The concerned Divisional Commissioner / CEO, Zilla Parishad should immediately engage the concerned officer and submit the compliance report to the Government by e-mail.
By order and in the name of the Governor of Maharashtra,
